# tvOS brand asset catalog (App Icon & image sets)

## `App Icon & Top Shelf Image.brandassets`

- The **App Store** app icon entry (**`App Icon - App Store.imagestack`**, **1280×768**) requires layers that **fill that stack**. **Do not** reuse **400×240** primary icon PNGs there or leave **empty** `Content.imageset` slots — **`actool`** errors (*last image stack layer … must exactly fill the image stack*) and related **IBAppleTVFramework-*** issues follow.
- If no **1280×768** layered art exists yet, **remove** that asset from **`Contents.json`** (and the folder) until art is ready — a single **400×240** primary icon can still build locally.

## Raster image sets (non-brand)

- For a **tvOS-only** target, prefer **`"idiom" : "tv"`** and explicit **`scale`** (e.g. **`1x`**) instead of **`universal`** when there is no iOS counterpart, to reduce ambiguous slot resolution.

